Package ca.ualberta.cmput301w13t11.FoodBook.model

Interface Summary
FView<M extends FModel> Generic View interface -- has only the update() method which is dependent upon the Model M this View is observing.
 

Class Summary
ClientHelper Helper class -- responsible for transforming HTTP response into Java Objects and vice-versa in service of the ServerClient.
DbManager Singleton class that manages the application's database.
DbOpenHelper Database helper class.
EmailSender Class responsible for e-mailing a recipe.
FModel<V extends FView> Generic model class -- essentially implements the same functionality as the Java "Observable" class.
Ingredient Class which models an ingredient (as part of a recipe, or in the User's MyIngredients Db).
IngredientsDbManager Implements the functionality required to manage the Ingredients database, which is the User maintained database of ingredients meant to reflect the contents of their kitchen.
Photo Class representing a photo object.
Recipe Class which models a recipe.
RecipesDbManager Implements the functionality required to manage the table of Recipes for the application.
ResultsDbManager Implements the functionality required to manage the Results database, which stores the results of the latest search query.
SearchHits<T> A class modeling the hits associated with a seach query to the ElasticSearch sever.
ServerClient Communicates with the server to perform searches, upload recipes and upload photos to recipes.
ServerPhoto Photo type to be used by Server Recipe -- its constructor makes an explicit conversion from Photo to ServerPhoto.
ServerRecipe A recipe class that can be written directly to the server -- ie.
ServerResponse<T> A class modeling a response to a POST by the server.
ServerSearchResponse<T> A class modeling a response to a search query returned from the server.
User Models a user of the application.
 

Enum Summary
ServerClient.ReturnCode Return codes possible for a networking task.
